Yes, I wondered about that.  Is it just that the function<p><pre><code>  func (w *Writer, int n) {
  }
</code></pre>
is actually a method, like:<p><pre><code>  func (w *Writer) Anon(int n) {
  }</code></pre>

Not really. Imagine if HTML was implemented as JSON. Consider a hyperlink:<p><pre><code>  { 'a' : 
    { 
     'attributes' : { 'href' : 'http://www.google.com/' },
     'val' : 'Google Search Engine' 
    }
  }
</code></pre>
That's insanity when compared to an XML format:<p><pre><code>  <a href="http://www.google.com/">Google Search Engine</a>
</code></pre>
XML is actually a great hypermedia format. It just got a bad wrap with SOAP, WSDL, etc.
